items.notes:
Based on the Wasserkuppe 5-day “Compact Glider Course” details, here are the **updated, targeted questions** to email before you commit:

---

## A. Course Content & Training Progression  
1. **Daily Flight Capacity**  
   - The brochure says “All You Can Fly.” Is there any soft cap on daily flights if the weather’s good (e.g. max launches per day)?  ([Gliding compact course at the Wasserkuppe flying school](https://fliegerschule-wasserkuppe.de/en/segelflug-kompaktkurs-wasserkuppe/))  
2. **Instructor Pairing**  
   - Will I have the same instructor all week? What’s your student-to-instructor ratio?  
3. **Winch-Only Launch vs. Aerotow Option**  
   - The compact course uses winch to maximize sorties. If I later want aerotow training (e.g. for cross-country), can I switch—at what additional cost?  
4. **Simulator Use**  
   - On weather-off days, how many hours on the gliding simulator are included? Any extra simulator slots available?  

## B. Solo Qualification & Beyond  
5. **Realistic Solo Timeline**  
   - You suggest solo in ~2 weeks (compact + daily training). For an English-only student, what’s the typical solo-qualification timeline at Wasserkuppe?  
6. **Post-Course Refresher Policy**  
   - If I don’t solo by day 5, can I “top up” with extra individual sessions at the same instructor rate?  

## C. Medical & Exam Support  
7. **Medical Certificate Assistance**  
   - I understand I need a medical before first solo. Do you help book the LBA aviation-medical examiner, or recommend local doctors?  
8. **Theory Integration**  
   - Do you offer any on-site English briefing or mock exams for the SPL theory, or partner with an e-learning provider?  

## D. Logistics, Meals & Accommodation  
9. **Dietary Requirements**  
   - Meals (breakfast & lunch) are included at Weltensegler. Can you cater to vegetarian/vegan or other dietary needs?  
10. **Accommodation Booking**  
   - Does the school handle my booking (using PAPILLON25) at the recommended hotels/holiday village, or must I book directly?  
11. **Weather-Cancellation Policy**  
   - If multiple days are grounded by weather, do you extend my course week at no extra charge?  

## E. Costs, Payments & Terms  
12. **Deposit & Refund Terms**  
   - You require a €600 deposit. What’s your refund policy if I must cancel more than X weeks before the course?  
13. **General Terms & Conditions**  
   - Are there any clauses in your GTC around additional fees (e.g. landing fees beyond winch, late-cancellation charges, equipment damage)?  

---

  Send this list to **info@flugschule-wasserkuppe.de** (or via their contact form) and compare how thoroughly—and promptly—they respond. That will give you a clear picture of their professionalism, English-support level, and flexibility before you sign up. Good luck!
